title: 110spc4 PSY 1
source_name_ch1: B. japonicum wild-type strain grown aerobically
growth_protocol_ch1: B. japonicum cells were grown aerobically to mid-exponential phase (OD600 0.5 to 0.7) in PSY medium. For microarray experiments with carbon-starved cells, cultures were pre-grown and further incubated for 24 h in minimal medium lacking a carbon source .
description: B. japonicum wild-type strain grown aerobically
data_processing: Signal intensities were detected and analyzed with MAS5 statistical algorithm (http://www.affymetrix.com). Normalized signal values from the arrays were then processed using Genespring GX 7.3 (Agilent Technologies,CA, USA). Only those probe sets that were called "present" or "marginal" in two of the three replicates were considered for further analysis. The experiment was normalized with the default settings for Affymetrix arrays, i.e., first data transformation to set measurements of below 0.01 to 0.01 followed by a per-chip normalization to the 50th percentile and a per-gene normalization to median. For statistical comparisons, the student t-test with a P value threshold of 0.01 was applied. Genes were considered as differentially expressed if the fold change (FC) was higher than 2 when comparing the different strains.

title: H1 mutant nodules soybean 21 Days 1
source_name_ch1: nodules soybean 21 dpi infected by B. diazoefficiens nifH mutant strain H1
growth_protocol_ch1: B. diazoefficiens-induced nodules from 5 soybean plants were collected for each GeneChip hybridization experiment. Nodules were harvested at 21 days post inoculation (dpi) and immediately frozen in liquid nitrogen.
description: nodules soybean 21 dpi infected by B. diazoefficiens nifH mutant strain H1
data_processing: Signal intensities were detected and analyzed with MAS5 statistical algorithm (http://www.affymetrix.com). Normalized signal values from the arrays were then processed using Genespring GX 7.3 (Agilent Technologies,CA, USA).  in 80% of all replicates were further considered. Moreover, we excluded all genes in analyses with bacteroids for which the expression was not at least two times higher than in the control hybridizations with root material only. Thereby, we excluded those signals that might have originated from cross-hybridization with plant RNA. For these cross-hybridization control experiments, the amount of plant RNA was normalized to the signal of the Glycine max 18S rRNA. For experiments comparing different conditions amongst bacteroids, each chip was normalized to the median. Values below 0.01 were set to 0.01. For statistical comparisons, the student t-test with a P-value threshold of 0.01 was applied. Genes were considered as differentially expressed if the fold change (FC) was higher than 2, when comparing different conditions amongst symbiotic bacteria.
